value.name: TESS search for donor-star pulsations in high-mass X-ray binaries
value.snippet: The detrended light curve of HD 249179 (Fig. C2) shows a quasi-periodic signal on a period of ∼0.28 d. This light curve also highlights how the amplitude of the short-period modulation increases by a factor of ∼3 at the same time as the start of the optical outburst.

value.name: A TESS search for donor-star pulsations in high-mass X-ray binaries
value.snippet: In two systems, V725 Tau and HD 249179 (which may not be an HMXB), we find evidence for an outburst, the former being simultaneous with an X-ray flare. We search for changes in the power spectra over the outburst duration and compare them with outbursts seen in other Be systems.
